  "text": "The error string 'mvcc: required revision has been compacted' originates from the etcd distributed key-value store. The ErrCompacted error variable is defined in server/storage/mvcc/kvstore.go at line 37 as a module-level variable in the mvcc package. This error is returned by the core rangeKeys function in server/storage/mvcc/kvstore_txn.go at line 81. The rangeKeys function is a method on the storeTxnCommon type that handles range queries over key-value pairs. It checks if the requested revision (rev) is less than the compacted main revision (tr.s.compactMainRev), and if so, returns the ErrCompacted error, indicating that the client has requested a revision that has been garbage-collected by the compaction process. This is a critical error case in etcd's MVCC (Multi-Version Concurrency Control) storage layer that prevents clients from accessing data that has been removed during compaction."
}

